// test/sema/resolution/global_scope.test — global-scope resolution
// fixture (T023 rollover; specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md Phase 4a).
// Asserts that struct-type declarations and top-level params declared
// at the global scope are resolvable from references inside a
// `module` block.
//
// Per `emit-ast-format.contract.md` Invariants 2 + 3: every name-ref
// gains a `: <Type>` suffix and (when resolved) a
// ` -> decl@<file>:<line>:<col>` suffix pointing at the declaration
// site (ASCII separators per Invariant 7).
//
// Phase 4a status: this fixture exercises Phase 3's ResolutionPass on
// the global-scope path (struct-type declared then referenced by
// struct-instance-reg `s_t reg slot;`). The Phase 3 implementation
// already opens a Global scope in `runResolutionPass`; this fixture
// is the corpus rollover from that representative coverage.

// RUN: printf 'struct s_t { v[8]; };\nmodule m {\n  s_t reg slot;\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (StructDecl {{.*}}name=s_t
// CHECK: (ModuleBlock {{.*}}name=m
// CHECK: (StructInstDecl
